Example XML entry requried in applicationContext.xml file

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<beans xmlns="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="
        http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans/spring-beans.xsd">

    <!-- bean definitions here -->

</beans>

The schema above define the Bean definition which will validate the beans defined by us. Acts like a dictionary which we can use to define properties
of our bean.
Beans are
    esentially classes(POJOs).
    Replaces keyword new
    Define class, use the interface

